---
import Layout from "~/layouts/Layout.astro";

import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import flower1 from "~/assets/flower1.svg";
import grass3 from "~/assets/grass3.svg";

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl p-8 lg:py-12">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
      <Image src={flower1} alt="" class="h-12 w-auto" />
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">page webring</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg text-pretty text-neutral-600">
      <p>
        in autumn 2025, as the leaves fell and the air turned crisp, teens in
        Hack Club spent 2 months designing and making their own personal
        website, as part of the
        <a
          href="https://page.hackclub.com"
          class="text-link font-semibold underline decoration-wavy [text-decoration-skip-ink:none] hover:text-teal-800"
          >personal website ysws event</a
        >. these sites gave an outlet for them to showcase themselves, their
        hobbies and their interests to the world.
      </p>
      <p>
        this webring is a collection of those personal websites, so people (like
        you!!) can go explore, find new friends, and get inspiration for making
        your own personal site.
      </p>
    </div>
    <a href="/to/random" class="group inline-block">
      <div
        class="border-border text-border relative isolate mt-4 flex h-10 w-max items-center border-2 bg-white px-3 font-semibold shadow-xs transition group-hover:text-white group-active:scale-95 group-active:border-fuchsia-900"
      >
        <div
          class="bg-border absolute inset-0 -z-10 block origin-right transition not-group-hover:scale-x-0 group-hover:origin-left group-active:bg-fuchsia-900"
        >
        </div>
        enter the webring â†’
      </div>
    </a>

    <section class="mt-10 border-t-2 border-dashed border-neutral-200 pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">join</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        made a personal website? part of hack club? dm
        <a
          href="https://hackclub.enterprise.slack.com/team/U09D42Q0ARJ"
          class="mx-0.5 rounded-xs border border-cyan-200 bg-cyan-100 px-1 py-1 font-semibold text-cyan-700 transition hover:bg-cyan-200/75"
        >
          @gideon</a
        >
        to get added!
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">you should include:</p>
      <ul class="mt-1.5 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-6 text-neutral-600">
        <li>your preferred name or username</li>
        <li>a link to your amazing personal website</li>
        <li>
          an 88x31 button! either as an image, or a link to it hosted on your
          website
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        don't have a button yet? make one! you can use a design tool like
        <a
          href="https://figma.com"
          class="text-link font-semibold underline decoration-wavy [text-decoration-skip-ink:none] hover:text-teal-800"
          >Figma</a
        >, a pixel art editor like
        <a
          href="https://www.aseprite.org/"
          class="text-link font-semibold underline decoration-wavy [text-decoration-skip-ink:none] hover:text-teal-800"
          >Aseprite</a
        >, or generate one online, for example
        <a
          href="https://hekate2.github.io/buttonmaker/"
          class="text-link font-semibold underline decoration-wavy [text-decoration-skip-ink:none] hover:text-teal-800"
          >here</a
        >
        or
        <a
          href="http://88x31.datakra.sh/"
          class="text-link font-semibold underline decoration-wavy [text-decoration-skip-ink:none] hover:text-teal-800"
          >here</a
        >. make sure it's an image 88px wide and 31px tall, and remember to be
        creative!
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10 border-t-2 border-dashed border-neutral-200 pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">include</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        next you want to include the webring on your personal website! it's
        super easy, just add this script tag to the very end of your website's
        body:
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `<script src="https://example.com/embed.js"></script>`}</code></pre>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        then, wherever you want the webring link to appear in your page, add:
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `<pagering-link></pagering-link>`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10 border-t-2 border-dashed border-neutral-200 pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">api</h2>
      <div class="my-4 border-l-2 border-orange-500 bg-orange-100 p-3">
        <p class="text-orange-800">
          if you're using the api instead, <strong class="font-semibold"
            >still include the {"<script>"} tag on your page!</strong
          >
          it shows the overlay that allows you to navigate between websites.
        </p>
        <pre
          class="mt-2 border-2 border-orange-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm"><code>{
          `<script src="https://example.com/embed.js"></script>`}</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        <strong class="font-semibold text-black">GET /to/random:</strong> redirect
        to a random member of the webring
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `302 Found (redirect)`}</code></pre>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        <strong class="font-semibold text-black">GET /to/[id]:</strong> redirect to
        a specific member in the webring by id
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `302 Found (redirect)`}</code></pre>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        <strong class="font-semibold text-black">GET /to/[id]/next:</strong> redirect
        to the next member in the webring
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `302 Found (redirect)`}</code></pre>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        <strong class="font-semibold text-black">GET /to/[id]/prev:</strong> redirect
        to the previous member in the webring
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `302 Found (redirect)`}</code></pre>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        <strong class="font-semibold text-black">GET /api/v1/members:</strong> get
        all members of the webring
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `[
  {
    "id": "acon",
    "name": "acon",
    "url": "https://aconlin.com",
    "buttonUrl": "/buttons/acon.gif"
  },
  ...
]`}</code></pre>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        <strong class="font-semibold text-black"
          >GET /api/v1/members/[id]:</strong
        > get a specific member by id, and the previous and next members
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `{
  "current": {
    "id": "acon",
    "name": "acon",
    "url": "https://aconlin.com",
    "buttonUrl": "/buttons/acon.gif"
  },
  "prev": { ... },
  "next": { ... }
}`}</code></pre>
      <p class="mt-2 text-neutral-600">
        <strong class="font-semibold text-black">GET /api/v1/embed:</strong> get all
        members, and the current, previous, and next members for the current site.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-0.5 text-xs text-neutral-600">
        If you're calling this from a server, set your 'Origin' header to your
        site's URL (including http:// or https://)
      </p>
      <pre
        class="my-4 border-2 border-neutral-300 bg-white p-2 px-3 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-800"><code>{
          `{
  "current": {
    "id": "acon",
    "name": "acon",
    "url": "https://aconlin.com",
    "buttonUrl": "/buttons/acon.gif"
  },
  "prev": { ... },
  "next": { ... },
  "members": [ ... ]
}`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10 border-t-2 border-dashed border-neutral-200 pt-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 grayscale">
        made with ðŸ©¶ and ðŸ’» in hack club by heygideon. personal website ysws by
        acon.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <div class="aspect-1440/68 w-full"></div>
  <div class="fixed inset-x-0 bottom-0 bg-linear-to-t from-white via-white/80">
    <Image src={grass3} alt="" role="presentation" class="w-full" />
  </div>
</Layout>
